Type <code>Dict[str, str]</code> Default <code>{"TOP": "TOP", "FRONT": "FRONT", "LEFT": "LEFT", "BACK": "BACK", "RIGHT": "RIGHT", "BOTTOM": "BOTTOM"}</code> Description Display text for each main face. Only the six main faces have labels — edges and corners don't. Keys must be exactly: <code>TOP</code>, <code>FRONT</code>, <code>LEFT</code>, <code>BACK</code>, <code>RIGHT</code>, <code>BOTTOM</code>. <pre><code># German labels
style = NavCubeStyle(labels={
    "TOP": "OBEN", "FRONT": "VORNE", "LEFT": "LINKS",
    "BACK": "HINTEN", "RIGHT": "RECHTS", "BOTTOM": "UNTEN",
})

# Japanese labels
style = NavCubeStyle(
    font_family="Noto Sans CJK JP",
    labels={
        "TOP": "\u4e0a", "FRONT": "\u524d", "LEFT": "\u5de6",
        "BACK": "\u5f8c", "RIGHT": "\u53f3", "BOTTOM": "\u4e0b",
    },
)
</code></pre>
